cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SY

This paper proposes a method to impose linear inequality constraints on neural network activations, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on training neural networks with constraints. The second likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper discusses incorporating prior knowledge into the model. The third likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as the paper experiments with a constrained generative model. The fourth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper deals with neural networks. The fifth likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper discusses the speed-up of inference at test time.
